[
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Ellicott's Commentary for English Readers",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(27) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Burnt the city with fire.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "—This was unusual, for we are told that Hazor was the only city which Joshua burnt (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Joshua 11:13",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). Perhaps they had devoted the city by a ban, as Jericho was devoted (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Joshua 6:24",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "); or the burning may have been due to policy or to accident. Probably the notion that such conduct was cruel and unjustifiable never occurred to them; nor must we judge them by the standard of Christian times. But Dan was no gainer. His name disappears from the records of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1Chronicles 4:1",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", and he is not mentioned among the elected tribes in Revelation 7. Blunt (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Undesigned Coincidences, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "pt. 2, 4) conjectures, from ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2Chronicles 2:14",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", that the cause of their disappearance from Israelite records—the latest mention of them as a tribe being in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1Chronicles 27:22",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "—was due to their intermarriages with the Phœnicians.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Jdg 18:27-29",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Jdg 18:27-29",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "And burned the city with fire — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Not wholly, but in a great measure, to make their conquest more easy. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "They built a city — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Or, rather, repaired and enlarged that which they found there. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "After the name of Dan — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "That it might be manifest they belonged to the tribe of Dan, though they were settled at a great distance from them in the most northerly part of the land; whereas the lot of their tribe was in the southern part of Canaan.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Matthew Henry's Concise Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "17:7-13 Micah thought it was a sign of God's favour to him and his images, that a Levite should come to his door. Thus those who please themselves with their own delusions, if Providence unexpectedly bring any thing to their hands that further them in their evil way, are apt from thence to think that God is pleased with them.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
