  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Jamieson-Fausset-Brown Bible Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Jud 18:27-29. They Win Laish.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "27. they … came unto Laish … smote them—the inhabitants.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and burnt the city—\"We are revolted by this inroad and massacre of a quiet and secure people. Nevertheless, if the original grant of Canaan to the Israelites gave them the warrant of a divine commission and command for this enterprise, that sanctifies all and legalizes all\" [Chalmers]. This place seems to have been a dependency of Zidon, the distance of which, however, rendered it impossible to obtain aid thence in the sudden emergency.",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
