  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 27.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "And they",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". In the Hebrew the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "they is",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " emphatic. It would be better expressed in English by repeating ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "The children of Dan.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " The repetition of the epithets ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "quiet and secure",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", as applied to the people of Laish, rather seems to indicate the writer's reprobation of the deed as cruel, like that of Simeon and Levi in slaying Hamor and Shechem. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "They smote them with the edge of the sword",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - a phrase denoting an exterminating slaughter (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 34:26",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Joshua 19:47",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Samuel 15:8",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", etc.). ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "And they burnt the city",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", etc. Perhaps they had made the people and city a ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "cherem",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", a devoted thing, and therefore slew the one and burnt the other (cf. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Numbers 21:3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Joshua 8:19",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Joshua 11:11",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", etc.); or the burning of the city may have been one of the means by which they destroyed the people. Judges 18:27",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
