  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Keil and Delitzsch Biblical Commentary on the Old Testament",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And they (the Danites) had taken what Micah had made, i.e., his idols and his priest, and they fell upon Laish (על כּוא, to come over a person, to fall upon him, as in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Genesis 34:25",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), a people living quietly and free from care (vid., ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Judges 18:7",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), smote them with the edge of the sword (see at ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Genesis 34:26",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), and burned down the city (cf. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Joshua 6:24",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), as it had no deliverer in its isolated condition (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Judges 18:28",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; cf. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Judges 18:7",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). It was situated \"in the valley which stretches to Beth-rehob.\" This valley is the upper part of the Huleh lowland, through which the central source of the Jordan (Leddan) flows, and by which Laish-Dan, the present Tell el Kadi, stood (see at ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Joshua 19:47",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). Beth-rehob is most probably the same place as the Rehob mentioned in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Numbers 13:21",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", and the Beth-rehob of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Samuel 10:6",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", which is there used to designate a part of Syria, and for which Rehob only is also used in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Judges 18:8",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Robinson (Bibl. Res. pp. 371ff.) supposes it to be the castle of Hunin or Honin, on the south-west of Tell el Kadi; but this is hardly correct (see the remarks on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Numbers 13:21",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", Pent. p. 709). The city, which lay in ashes, was afterwards rebuilt by the Danites, and called Dan, from the name of the founder of their tribe; and the ruins are still to be seen, as already affirmed, on the southern slope of the Tell el Kadi (see Rob. Bibl. Res. pp. 391-2, and the comm. on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Joshua 19:47",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). ",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  }
]